---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Concrete Sleeper Retaining Walls Pakenham | 50+ Year Lifespan"
  description="Concrete sleeper retaining walls in Pakenham, Officer, Berwick & Cardinia Shire. Steel-reinforced concrete sleepers in galvanised H-posts. 50+ year lifespan, $400–$600/m². Free quote — (03) 9003 0223."
  canonical="https://pakenhamretainingwalls.com.au/services/concrete-sleeper-walls/">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Concrete Sleeper Walls</span>
      <h1>Concrete sleeper <span class="accent">retaining walls</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Steel-reinforced concrete sleepers slotted into galvanised H-posts. Built right,
        these walls outlast the house. The strongest, longest-lasting wall under
        $700/m&sup2; on the market.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030223">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0223</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why concrete sleeper</span>
      <h2>The right wall for Pakenham&rsquo;s reactive clay.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>

      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <p>
          Concrete sleeper walls have become the default residential wall across the
          Cardinia Shire over the last 10 years &mdash; and for good reason. The system
          tolerates wet clay, freeze-thaw cycles, termites, ground movement, and impact
          loads in ways that timber simply can&rsquo;t.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">How the system works</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Posts:</strong> 100&times;100&times;5mm hot-dipped galvanised steel H-posts, cored into 600mm-deep concrete footings (deeper for taller walls).</li>
          <li><strong>Sleepers:</strong> 200mm-thick steel-reinforced concrete sleepers, 50 MPa, slotted between the H-flanges as the wall builds up.</li>
          <li><strong>Drainage:</strong> 200mm of 20mm aggregate behind every wall, wrapped in geofabric, with 100mm slotted ag-pipe to a legal stormwater outlet.</li>
          <li><strong>Capping:</strong> optional concrete or stone cap on the top course for a finished look.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Finishes</h3>
        <p>
          Plain grey is the cheapest. We also do woodgrain texture (looks like sleeper
          timber but it&rsquo;s concrete), exposed aggregate, and stone-effect &mdash;
          all factory-cast, no painting.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Cost &amp; lifespan</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Cost:</strong> $400&ndash;$600/m&sup2; installed (includes drainage, footings, capping)</li>
          <li><strong>Lifespan:</strong> 50+ years &mdash; manufacturers warrant the sleepers themselves for 25 years</li>
          <li><strong>Maximum height:</strong> 2.4m unsupported, taller with engineering</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">When concrete sleeper is the right call</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Walls over 900mm where you don&rsquo;t want to rebuild in 20 years</li>
          <li>Damp ground where timber will rot fast</li>
          <li>High-traffic areas (driveway retaining, pool surrounds)</li>
          <li>Permit jobs where engineering certification is needed</li>
          <li>Replacing a failed timber wall</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other wall types.</h2>
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/timber-retaining-walls/"><h3>Timber sleeper</h3><p>Most economical, 15&ndash;40 year lifespan.</p><span class="svc-link">Details &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/block-retaining-walls/"><h3>Block / masonry</h3><p>Premium look, long lifespan.</p><span class="svc-link">Details &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/excavation-earthworks/"><h3>Earthworks</h3><p>Cut-and-fill, drainage, levelling.</p><span class="svc-link">Details &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/"><h3>Back to home</h3><p>Pakenham retaining walls overview.</p><span class="svc-link">Home &rarr;</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free concrete sleeper quote.</h2>
        <p>Site visit, fixed price, written quote within 48 hours.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030223">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0223</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Quote online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
